properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 7 at 3:49PM AKST until February 10 at 12:00AM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Strong gusty winds and blowing snow occuring. Snow
expected. Plan on difficult travel conditions. South winds
gusting to 60 mph and local areas of poor visibility in blowing
snow are occuring north of Carlo Creek. Storm total snow
accumulations of 12 inches are expected south of Carlo Creek,
with about 2 inches of snow north of Carlo Creek

* WHERE...Denali.

* WHEN...Until midnight Sunday night.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...North of Carlo Creek, south winds are now
gusting to 60 mph and causing blowing snow with areas of low
visibility. Little falling snow is expected north of Carlo
Creek. South of Carlo Creek, snow is expected develop tonight
and continue into Sunday along with blowing snow and areas of
low visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow and blowing snow means periods
of snow and blowing snow will cause travel difficulties. The
latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT AKST SUNDAY NIGHT
